{"id":"1805.04083","submitter":"Oleg Lychkovskiy","authors":"N. Il`in and O. Lychkovskiy","title":"Quantum speed limits for adiabatic evolution, Loschmidt echo and beyond","comments":"presented at the 14th IQSA Conference \"Quantum Structures 2018\"","journal-ref":"Int. J. Theor. Phys. 60, 640 (2021)","doi":"10.1007/s10773-020-04458-5","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  One often needs to estimate how fast an evolving state of a quantum system\ncan depart from some target state or target subspace of a Hilbert space. Such\nestimates are known as quantum speed limits. We derive a quantum speed limit\nfor a general time-dependent target subspace. When the target subspace is an\ninstantaneous invariant subspace of a time-dependent Hamiltonian, the obtained\nquantum speed limit bounds the adiabatic fidelity, which is a figure of merit\nof quantum adiabaticity. We also compare two states evolving under two\ndifferent Hamiltonians and derive a bound on the Loschmidt echo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 May 2018 17:41:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 13 Nov 2018 11:51:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 23 May 2020 16:33:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-04"}
